# Delivery, Admin, And Workflow Rules

- Keep all admin features inside Telegram Mini App; no separate admin site by default.
- Admin section visibility is role-based and hidden for non-admin users.
- Delivery flow must support both delivery and pickup, with staged CDEK integration.
- Start with mock delivery tariffs only where live API is not approved yet.
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits and describe user-facing intent.

## Release Discipline

- Before completion, verify changed flows manually or with tests.
- If a rule conflict appears, prioritize explicit product constraints from MURU rules.
- Do not change folder structure, payment policy, or core UX map without approval.
- Report what was verified, what remains mock/stub, and what requires next approval.
